        "type": "message",
        "text": "I'm working on <http:\/\/knotend.com|knotend.com> which is a keyboard-driven flowchart editor. I started thinking about this because I had a lot of large projects and I wanted a way to define dependencies between tasks. Most tools are pretty slow because they're mouse-based. Or they're code-based (like graphviz, mermaid), but not the same idea I was going for.\n\nIt has auto-layout and uses a grid to position nodes. There's a selection and navigation mechanism a bit like a spreadsheet to keep things keyboard-based. You can use it without an account and there's also video demos in the top left of the home page. I'd love some feedback from the community, thanks!",
